results.name: Two-column table read by rows: row n (n >= 1) gives a squarefree integer x and an integer y such that n = x*y^2.
program: (MAGMA) at:=0; for n in [1..100] do print Squarefree(n); end for;
xref: The two columns are A007913, A000188.
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Dec 23 2006
